KaFKA (kafka@desert.hacktic.nl) writes:

> The Norton Utilities come with a program called Diskreet.
> The US features two kinds of encryption: DES and a propriety
> encryption. The 'european' version has only propriety
> encryption.

That's kinda funny, because I got mine (with both DES and proprietary
encryption enabled) in Bulgaria... :-)

Anyway, the "security" of the DES implementation in Diskreet has been
recently analysed in an excellent article by Peter Gutmann. It is
available from our ftp site as

ftp.informatik.uni-hamburg.de:/pub/virus/texts/crypto/diskreet.zip

